(power_register, power_pad).explanation: These represent power consumption in different and independent components of the processor architecture, with register files and I/O pads serving distinct functions;

(power_register, time).explanation: Register file power consumption is a consequence of design choices and does not directly influence the execution time of programs;

(power_register, power_clock).explanation: These represent independent power consumption components in the processor, with clock distribution and register files being separate functional units;
